2/9. Paul Hacking. <em>The versal deformation of an isolated toric Gorenstein singularity</em>, by K. Altmann. <a href="http://www.math.fu-berlin.de/altmann/PAPER/versal.pdf">pdf</a>. 
<br>
<br>
2/16. Luca Schaffler. <em>The moduli space of 8 points on
P^1 and automorphic forms</em>, by S. Kondo. <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/math/0504233">arXiv</a>. 
<br>
<br>
2/23. Jenia Tevelev. <em>Rationality specializes in families</em>. <a href="http://www.math.umass.edu/calendar/reading-seminar-in-algebraic-geometry/17983">Abstract</a>. References:
<br>
<br>
J. Nicaise and E. Shinder, <em>The motivic nearby fiber and degeneration of stable rationality</em>, <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/1708.02790">arXiv</a>.
<br>
